# Glossary of Programming Terms

API
: Application Programming Interface
: A set of protocols and tools for building software applications

CI/CD
: Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment
: Practices for automating the build, test, and deployment pipeline

CRUD
: Create, Read, Update, Delete
: The four basic operations for persistent storage

DRY
: Don't Repeat Yourself
: A principle aimed at reducing duplication in code

KISS
: Keep It Simple, Stupid
: A design principle favoring simplicity over complexity

ORM
: Object-Relational Mapping
: A technique for converting between incompatible type systems in OOP languages

REST
: Representational State Transfer
: An architectural style for distributed hypermedia systems

SOLID
: Single responsibility, Open-closed, Liskov substitution, Interface segregation, Dependency inversion
: Five design principles for object-oriented programming

TDD
: Test-Driven Development
: A methodology where tests are written before the implementation code

YAGNI
: You Aren't Gonna Need It
: A principle stating that features should not be added until they are actually needed
